						<summary>

						<p>On a hero-stone set up in a mango groove owned by Doraisamy Naidu.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Parakēsarivarman, who took the head of Vīrapāṇḍya (Āditya II) Year 3: 963 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records that when the village Chōḷaṉūr was destroyed and its cattle was seized, Śāttayaṉ, the son of Vikramādittan alias Diṉmacheṭṭi, a sluice operator at Cheṅguṉṟam fought with that cattle lifter and died while rescuring the cattle.</p>						

						</summary>
